[[File:Toyohahsi Gion Matsuri 02.jpg|thumb|275px|Toyohashi Gion Festival – Fireworks Display]] '''Toyohashi Gion Festival''' (豊橋祇園祭) is a festival held every '''mid-July''' at {{ill|Yoshida Shrine (Toyohashi)|ja|吉田神社 (豊橋市)|12=draft|12=draft}} in '''Sekiwa Town (関屋町), Toyohashi City (豊橋市)'''.
The festival centers around the '''Mikoshi Togyo (神輿渡御, portable shrine procession)'''. Additionally, the '''Tezutsu Fireworks (手筒花火)''' on the night before the festival and the '''fireworks display''' on the eve of the main event are well known.
== Origin & History == [[File:Yoshida, Tenno Festival on the Fifteenth Day of the Sixth Month LACMA M.66.35.23.jpg|thumb|The Tenno Festival, by {{ill|Utagawa Hiroshige|ja|歌川広重|12=draft|12=draft}}]] The festival '''originated in the Edo period as the Tenno Festival (天王祭)'''. It is also depicted in the illustrated manuscript '''"Mikawa no Kuni Yoshida Meiseki Sōroku" (三河国吉田名跡綜録)''', authored by '''{{ill|Yamamoto Teishin|ja|山本貞晨|12=draft|12=draft}}''', which is kept at Yoshida Shrine.
The '''mikoshi procession''' is said to '''commemorate Minamoto no Yoritomo (源頼朝)''', with participants '''parading in Kamakura and Heian period attire'''.
Additionally, '''Tezutsu Fireworks''' are believed to have begun in '''Eiroku 1 (1558)''' when '''{{ill|Imagawa Yoshimoto|ja|今川義元|12=draft|12=draft}}’s Yoshida Castle governor, {{ill|Obara Shigetane|ja|小原鎮実|12=draft|12=draft}} (Ōhara Bizen no Kami, 大原備前守), dedicated them to Yoshida Shrine'''. A stone monument '''"Birthplace of the Traditional Mikawa Tezutsu Fireworks" (伝承三河伝統 手筒花火発祥之地)''' stands within the shrine grounds. The '''Ōzutsu Fireworks (大筒花火)''' are handcrafted by local neighborhood associations, and they '''parade them like mikoshi'''.
== Schedule == [[File:吉田天王社祭礼図.jpg|thumb|500px|Illustration of Yoshida Tenno Shrine Festival]] * '''Day Before (Thursday)''' ''' Children's '''Sasa Dance (笹踊り)''': 15:00–17:00
* '''First Day (Friday)''' ''' '''Yoimatsuri (宵祭り, Night Festival)''': From 18:00 ''' '''Shinzen Fireworks Dedication (神前花火奉納, Tezutsu Fireworks)''': From 18:45
* '''Second Day (Saturday)''' ''' '''Zenyasai (前夜祭, Fireworks Display Eve)''': From 18:00
* '''Final Day (Sunday)''' ''' '''Reisai Ceremony (例祭式典)''': From 10:00 – Includes the '''Kenpeishi Sankō (献幣使参向)''' and '''Urayasu no Mai (浦安の舞) dedication dance''' ''' '''Miyuki Festival (御幸祭, Mikoshi Procession)''': From 17:00 == See Also == * {{ill|Gion Festival|ja|祇園祭|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Yoshida Shrine (Toyohashi)|ja|吉田神社 (豊橋市)|12=draft|12=draft}}
== External Links == {{Commonscat|Toyohashi Gion Matsuri}} * [https://www.toyohashigion.org/ Official Website of the Toyohashi Gion Festival Sponsorship Association] * [https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/1190665/42 Fireworks Viewing in Toyohashi] – From *Tabi no Koguchō* (『旅の小遣帳』), Jiji Shinpo Family Section (1930)
